Author: Tracey Williams Kiesling
Content:
Question:

Wyman’s wild blueberries are not organic. Wal Mart has 3 lb bags of them but they’re not organic either. Where can we get organic wild blueberries???

Author: George Greek
Content: -Tracey Williams Kiesling Good point, but keep in mind that is what Medical Medium recommends.  Happy healing.

Author: Julia Serrago
Content: -Tracey Williams Kiesling MM has explained that this wild food is beyond organic. Plus Wymans almost never has to spray because the plants are so naturally powerful. Btw most organic farms spray too.

Author: Tracey Williams Kiesling
Content: --Julia Serrago ok thanks that really helps. I do get organic cilantro too. I wonder if all wild blueberries fit the bill. The Wal Mart ones are much less expensive.

Author: Melissa Reynolds Davis
Content: -Tracey Williams Kiesling trader Joe's has them. They're apparently just the same as the conventional ones. Wild blueberries are naturally pest resistant.

Author: Julie M Tussing
Content: --Melissa Reynolds Davis no wild are not the same as conventional

Author: Melissa Reynolds Davis
Content: --Julie M Tussing I meant the organically grown wild blueberries are the same as the conventionally grown wild blueberries.

Author: Julia Serrago
Content:
--Tracey Williams Kiesling while wymans (we know they hardly need to spray) is best I believe any wild blueberry is still powerful. I used to sometimes get TraderJoe’s brand. I will have to look at Walmart too thank you. 
If you’re near a BJ’s they have 4 pound bag same price as 3 pounds at grocery store. 
Keep up the great work!  🫐

Author: Mary Earhart
Content: -Tracey Williams Kiesling  Trader Joe’s says organic but they are from Canada, not Maine

Author: Barry Millsap
Content: No wild blueberries are organic.  Wild is a step beyond organic - better.

Author: FC Savla
Content: MM recommends that brand though it doesn't say organic.

Author: Sarah St Cyr
Content: Link To "Cleanse To Heal" Please! Link To Each MM book there Is!
